definitions: a slight error in a rotating tool, machine component, etc., such as being off-center or not exactly round

examples.text: slight runout in your drill can make the holes oversized

shortDefinitions: slight error in rotating tool, machine component

definitions: a length of time or stretch of ground over which something gradually ceases or is brought to an end or a halt

examples.text: I skied the trail's long runout to the bottom and found the familiar yellow bus waiting

shortDefinitions: length of time or stretch of ground over which something gradually ceases or is brought to end
